         As an idle response to a question posed about the new EoT vs the old Prenerf 49 pet. Ahahahahaha.. any day would I take the old 49 pet. Give him two FS daggers (or, *gasp* better weapons.. like the stun whips from Paw) and he would tear up an EoT so fast, he wouldn't take more than half 3/4 damage. (I'd say more than half, but I'm trying to be giving here). Do you even know what it was like to be 50 pre-Kunark? Holy christ man, the few necros (there really weren't that many back then that made 50 pre-kunark, most made it afterwards) that made 50 could stomp anything in the game at that time. (Ok, we couldn't solo the plains, but still) Lguk/Sol B and Naggy/Vox were the big things back then. Got a necro with you? Then you have more damage output than any Warrior had a prayer of putting out (and sure, that was probably unfair.. but that's beside the point). Anyway, Invoke Death (aka Bob) was insanely powerful. Wanna know how necros died back then? A mob ate their pet and then killed them? Ha! More often you died before your pet did because of a failed FD or something. Your pet was still kicking the crap out of the mob. Anyway, if you didn't experience, it's ok that you don't understand. Just don't preach it when you don't know it.<img src=icon_smile.gif border=0 align=middle></P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=205091" target="_blank"><font color=red><font size=5>Ashtaroth Solarium</font id=size5></font id=red></a><BR><i>Nec-Romancer of Innoruuk</i><BR><i>Legends of the Realm</i><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
